### **6.11.1 Files traced — important caveat (F-Stats-1 KEYSTONE)**

There is no src/models/CharacterState.js. ls src/models/ | grep -iE "^Character" returns 12 files, none of which back this table. grep -r "tableName.*character_state" src/models/ returns zero hits. Every read and write to character_state across the codebase is raw sequelize.query() against literal SQL strings. This is itself the zone’s headline finding (F-Stats-1), and reframes how the rest of the zone’s findings should be read: there is no model layer to anchor a fix against.

