## **11.5 F-Deploy-G1 findings registry (NEW v9)**

The F-Deploy-1 G1 audit (in progress on branch `claude/f-deploy-1-g1-audit`) filed 27 file:line findings across 7 §3 file-read/diagnostic sections. Severity distribution: 18 P0, 8 P1, 1 P2. Per §3 audit organization, findings cluster by file:

### §3.3 — `.github/workflows/deploy-dev.yml` (findings A-G)

| **ID** | **Severity** | **Subject** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| F-Deploy-G1-A | P0 | Path-ordering: PM2 binary unavailable in early build step (resolves later same run) |
| F-Deploy-G1-B | P0 | Dependency/runtime version delta on EC2 (npm ci installs newer express-rate-limit than dev local) |
| F-Deploy-G1-C | P0 | Non-fatal migration handling — `MIGRATION_FAILED=true` continues to PM2 restart (PRIMARY blocker for §2.6) |
| F-Deploy-G1-D | P1 | Disk-cleanup ordering precedes extraction, can fail mid-deploy |
| F-Deploy-G1-E | P1 | Smoke test sequence dumps logs but doesn't classify by severity |
| F-Deploy-G1-F | P0 | `/health` success does not imply route-level correctness (PM2 "online" + 500 on /api routes) |
| F-Deploy-G1-G | P0 | Dev and prod share single EC2 instance + PM2 process group — failed dev deploy can take down prod via `pm2 stop all` |

### §3.5 — `ecosystem.config.js` (findings H-J)

| **ID** | **Severity** | **Subject** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| F-Deploy-G1-H | P0 | Default `env` block on `episode-api` configures dev port 3002; production deploy requires `--env production` flag to get prod port 3000 (the §12.19 outage root cause) |
| F-Deploy-G1-I | P1 | `episode-worker` has no `env_production` block, runs in fork mode without environment override |
| F-Deploy-G1-J | P1 | No PM2 restart-policy difference between dev and prod (both unlimited restarts on crash) |

### §3.2 — `.github/workflows/auto-merge.yml` (findings K-O — workflow DELETED 2026-05-15)

| **ID** | **Severity** | **Subject** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| F-Deploy-G1-K | P0 | Workflow fires `gh pr merge --auto` on EVERY PR with no filter — affects all PRs regardless of source branch, content, or target |
| F-Deploy-G1-L | P0 | Draft PRs are not exempt from the auto-merge trigger |
| F-Deploy-G1-M | P0 | `--auto` timing is out-of-band: queues merge until required checks pass; with zero required checks (F-Deploy-G1-V), fires immediately |
| F-Deploy-G1-N | P1 | No author/origin verification: workflow uses `${{ secrets.GITHUB_TOKEN }}` which auto-passes branch protection if owner is the actor |
| F-Deploy-G1-O | P1 | No logging of decision rationale — silent merges with no audit trail |

### §3.1 — `.github/workflows/auto-merge-to-dev.yml` (findings P-R)

| **ID** | **Severity** | **Subject** |
